issue.body:
In PhpStorm and other tools, it's typical to be able to hint globals similar to how you do variables, like:

```php
function a() {
    /** @var string $token */
    global $token;
    echo $token;
}
```

In Psalm, this doesn't seem to be supported.

Leading on from #3794, I sometimes find myself want to explicitly declare a variable's type at some point in the control flow. It might be that the Psalm types can't quite express the logic, but I _know_ a type of a var all the same.

It would be useful to be able to declare / update a variable type at any point by doing `/** @var string $myvar */`. Currently I have to do a workaround like this:

```php
$myvar = some_func();

if ( $myvar === 'bye' ) {
    exit;
}

// I know the type of $myvar is now int
/** @var int */
$myvar = $myvar;
```

It would be a lot better to be able to do:

```php
$myvar = some_func();

if ( $myvar === 'bye' ) {
    exit;
}

// I know the type of $myvar is now int
/** @var int $myvar */
```

